The reaction proceeds with the formation of active site C(O) that later is converted to carbon–oxygen complex, which provides oxygen for the photocatalytic reaction. SO2 reacts with the holes and O2 from the CeO2, and is thereby converted to SO3 (Fig. 9). The electrons on the surface of the catalyst react with the carbon–oxygen complex, simultaneously CeO2 retains the O2 and generates carbon [20].2CeO2+xSO2→xSO3+CeO2-x\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
